{
  "text": "If we quantify the cost of network communication by the number of tuples moved to remote nodes, then the cost of three schedules in Figure 1 will be 8 (i.e., 3+1+2+1+1), 7, and 6 respectively. Within the scope of current study in the filed of data management (e.g., [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] ), the schedule plan SP 2 will be considered as an optimal solution and chosen by underlying systems, because it transfers less data than other two approaches.",
  "correct_citation": {
